    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche buns</strong> in half</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> brioche halves</strong> to the pan, cut-side down, and cook for 3-4 min or until toasted and golden</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Once golden, transfer to a plate and set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1619784892600-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1619784892600-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1619784892600-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1619784892600-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1619784892600-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>(enough to cover the whole base of the pan)</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>and cook for 8-10 min, turning frequently, or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy chicken</strong></p><p>Tip: Add more oil to the pan if it is looking a little dry</p><p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1-1619784903549-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1-1619784903549-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1-1619784903549-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1-1619784903549-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1-1619784903549-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>crispy chicken</strong> to a plate covered with kitchen paper and carefully pour away any excess oil</p><p>Return the pan to a low heat, add the <strong>fiery Marmite glaze</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until starting to thicken</p><p>Return the<strong> crispy chicken</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up until nicely coated in the glaze – this is your <strong>fiery Marmite-glazed chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1619784920214-x200.jpg",
